Phoenix Project
Historgram Example Application Readme
Last revised 15th April 2007


1. Application Overview
-----------------------

The histogram application generates the histogram of frequencies of pixel values
in the red, green and blue channels of a bitmap picture.


2. Provided Files
-----------------

hist-pthread.c: The pthread version of the application
stddefines.h: Contains declarations of commonly used functions and constants
datafiles/*.bmp: Sample bitmap files of varying sizes that can be used as 
                 input to this application
README: This file


3. Running the Application
--------------------------

run 'clang hist-pthread.c -lpthread -o hist-pthread' to compile the pthread version of the application. Then, to execute the program run the following command, 

./hist-pthread <image-name>

